230
0:11:10.544,000 --> 0:11:13,000
We reminded them that when workers have more money,

231
0:11:14.11,000 --> 0:11:15,000
businesses have more customers,

232
0:11:15.822,000 --> 0:11:16,000
and need more employees.

233
0:11:17.804,000 --> 0:11:19,000
We reminded them that when businesses

234
0:11:20.49,000 --> 0:11:22,000
pay workers a living wage,

235
0:11:23.21,000 --> 0:11:24,000
taxpayers are relieved of the burden

236
0:11:25.102,000 --> 0:11:26,000
of funding the poverty programs

237
0:11:26.812,000 --> 0:11:28,000
like food stamps and medical assistance

238
0:11:29.714,000 --> 0:11:3,000
and rent assistance

239
0:11:31.424,000 --> 0:11:33,000
that those workers need.

240
0:11:33.82,000 --> 0:11:35,000
We reminded them that low-wage workers

241
0:11:36.784,000 --> 0:11:38,000
make terrible taxpayers,

242
0:11:39.11,000 --> 0:11:41,000
and that when you raise the minimum wage

243
0:11:41.128,000 --> 0:11:43,000
for all businesses,

244
0:11:43.253,000 --> 0:11:44,000
all businesses benefit

245
0:11:44.92,000 --> 0:11:46,000
