outsource its CEO's job, automate their job,

261
0:12:31.18,000 --> 0:12:33,000
export the job to China.

262
0:12:33.267,000 --> 0:12:35,000
In fact, we appear to be employing

263
0:12:35.293,000 --> 0:12:38,000
more CEOs and senior managers than ever before.

264
0:12:38.515,000 --> 0:12:42,000
So too for technology workers

265
0:12:42.705,000 --> 0:12:43,000
and financial services workers,

266
0:12:44.531,000 --> 0:12:46,000
who earn multiples of the median wage

267
0:12:47.149,000 --> 0:12:49,000
and yet we employ more and more of them,

268
0:12:49.154,000 --> 0:12:53,000
so clearly you can raise the price of employment

269
0:12:54.05,000 --> 0:12:56,000
and get more of it.

270
0:12:56.091,000 --> 0:12:58,000
I know that most people

271
0:12:58.675,000 --> 0:12:59,000
think that the $15 minimum wage

272
0:13:00.397,000 --> 0:13:03,000
is this insane, risky economic experiment.

273
0:13:04.312,000 --> 0:13:05,000
We disagree.

274
0:13:06.21,000 --> 0:13:08,000
We believe that the $15 minimum wage

275
0:13:08.684,000 --> 0:13:09,000
in Seattle

276
0:13:09.95,000 --> 0:13:1,000
is actually the continuation

277
0:13:11.803,000 --> 0:13:13,000
of a logical economic policy.

278
0:13:14.511,000 --> 0:13:15,000
It is allowing our city

279
0:13:16.471,000 --> 0:13:18,000
to kick your city's ass.

280
0:13:19.206,000 --> 0:13:2,000
Because, you see,

281
0:13:20.965,000 --> 0:13:21,000
Washington state already has

282
0:13:22.677,000 --> 0:13:23,000
the highest minimum wage

283
0:13:24.17,000 --> 0:13:25,000
of any state in the nation.

284
0:13:25.869,000 --> 0:13:27,000
We pay all workers $9.32,

285
0:13:28.13,000 --> 0:13:29,000
which is almost 30 percent more

286
0:13:29.973,000 --> 0:13:31,000
than the federal minimum of 7.25,

287
0:13:32.531,000 --> 0:13:35,000
but crucially, 427 percent more

288
0:13:36.484,000 --> 0:13:39,000
than the federal tipped minimum of 2.13.

289
0:13:40.07,000 --> 0:13:42,000
If trickle-down thinkers were right,

290
0:13:42.686,000 --> 0:13:45,000
then Washington state should have massive unemployment.

291
0:13:45.798,000 --> 0:13:47,000
Seattle should be sliding into the ocean.

292
0:13:48.478,000 --> 0:13:51,000
And yet, Seattle

293
0:13:51.501,000 --> 0:13:54,000
is the fastest-growing big city in the country.

294
0:13:55.399,000 --> 0:13:59,000
Washington state is generating small business jobs

295
0:13:59.516,000 --> 0:14:01,000
at a higher rate than any other major state

296
0:14:02.137,000 --> 0:14:03,000
in the nation.

297
0:14:03.993,000 --> 0:14:06,000
The restaurant business in Seattle? Booming.

298
0:14:07.897,000 --> 0:14:11,000
Why? Because the fundamental law of capitalism is,

299
0:14:12.285,000 --> 0:14:13,000
when workers have more money,

300
0:14:13.9,000 --> 0:14:14,000
businesses have more customers

301
0:14:15.426,000 --> 0:14:17,000
and need more workers.

302
0:14:17.683,000 --> 0:14:2,000
When restaurants pay restaurant workers enough

303
0:14:20.834,000 --> 0:14:23,000
so that even they can afford to eat in restaurants,

304
0:14:24.456,000 --> 0:14:26,000
that's not bad for the restaurant business.

305
0:14:27.121,000 --> 0:14:28,000
That's good for it,

306
0:14:28.82,000 --> 0:14:32,000
despite what some restaurateurs may tell you.

307
0:14:33.399,000 --> 0:14:35,000
Is it more complicated than I'm making out?

308
0:14:35.457,000 --> 0:14:35,000
Of course it is.

309
0:14:36.454,000 --> 0:14:37,000
There are a lot of dynamics at play.

310
0:14:38.322,000 --> 0:14:4,000
But can we please stop insisting

311
0:14:40.564,000 --> 0:14:42,000
that if low-wage workers earn a little bit more,

312
0:14:43.365,000 --> 0:14:44,000
unemployment will skyrocket

313
0:14:44.873,000 --> 0:14:45,000
and the economy will collapse?

314
0:14:46.201,000 --> 0:14:48,000
There is no evidence for it.

315
0:14:48.81,000 --> 0:14:49,000
The most insidious thing

316
0:14:50.041,000 --> 0:14:51,000
about trickle-down economics

317
0:14:51.888,000 --> 0:14:53,000
is not the claim that if the rich get richer,

318
0:14:54.19,000 --> 0:14:55,000
everyone is better off.

319
0:14:55.727,000 --> 0:14:58,000
It is the claim made by those who oppose

320
0:14:58.788,000 --> 0:14:59,000
any increase in the minimum wage

321
0:15:00.69,000 --> 0:15:01,000
that if the poor get richer,

322
0:15:02.545,000 --> 0:15:04,000
that will be bad for the economy.

323
0:15:04.762,000 --> 0:15:05,000
This is nonsense.

324
0:15:06.742,000 --> 0:15:09,000
So can we please dispense with this rhetoric

325
0:15:10.607,000 --> 0:15:12,000
that says that rich guys like me

326
0:15:12.95,000 --> 0:15:14,000
and my plutocrat friends

327
0:15:15.804,000 --> 0:15:17,000
made our country?

328
0:15:18.377,000 --> 0:15:2,000
We plutocrats know,

329
0:15:20.452,000 --> 0:15:21,000
even if we don't like to admit it in public,

330
0:15:22.076,000 --> 0:15:24,000
that if we had been born somewhere else,

331
0:15:24.745,000 --> 0:15:25,000
not here in the United States,

332
0:15:26.642,000 --> 0:15:28,000
we might very well be just some dude standing barefoot

333
0:15:29.502,000 --> 0:15:32,000
by the side of a dirt road selling fruit.

334
0:15:32.652,000 --> 0:15:34,000
It's not that they don't have good entrepreneurs in other places,

335
0:15:35.183,000 --> 0:15:37,000
even very, very poor places.

336
0:15:37.208,000 --> 0:15:38,000
It's just that that's all

337
0:15:38.76,000 --> 0:15:42,000
that those entrepreneurs' customers can afford.

338
0:15:43.296,000 --> 0:15:47,000
So here's an idea for a new kind of economics,

339
0:15:47.895,000 --> 0:15:48,000
a new kind of politics

340
0:15:49.442,000 --> 0:15:51,000
that I call new capitalism.

341
0:15:52.329,000 --> 0:15:54,000
Let's acknowledge that capitalism

342
0:15:54.801,000 --> 0:15:55,000
beats the alternatives,

343
0:15:56.598,000 --> 0:15:59,000
but also that the more people we include,

344
0:16:00.595,000 --> 0:16:03,000
both as entrepreneurs and as customers,

345
0:16:04.119,000 --> 0:16:06,000
the better it works.

346
0:16:06.279,000 --> 0:16:09,000
Let's by all means shrink the size of government,

347
0:16:10.065,000 --> 0:16:12,000
but not by slashing the poverty programs,

348
0:16:12.784,000 --> 0:16:14,000
but by ensuring that workers are paid enough

349
0:16:14.801,000 --> 0:16:17,000
so that they actually don't need those programs.

350
0:16:18.123,000 --> 0:16:2,000
Let's invest enough in the middle class

351
0:16:21.04,000 --> 0:16:24,000
to make our economy fairer and more inclusive,

352
0:16:24.233,000 --> 0:16:27,000
and by fairer, more truly competitive,

353
0:16:28.167,000 --> 0:16:29,000
and by more truly competitive,

354
0:16:29.929,000 --> 0:16:31,000
more able to generate the solutions

355
0:16:32.745,000 --> 0:16:33,000
to human problems

356
0:16:34.217,000 --> 0:16:39,000
that are the true drivers of growth and prosperity.

357
0:16:39.847,000 --> 0:16:42,000
Capitalism is the greatest social technology

358
0:16:43.12,000 --> 0:16:44,000
ever invented

359
0:16:44.589,000 --> 0:16:46,000
for creating prosperity in human societies,

360
0:16:47.451,000 --> 0:16:48,000
if it is well managed,

361
0:16:49.185,000 --> 0:16:52,000
but capitalism, because of the fundamental

362
0:16:52.356,000 --> 0:16:54,000
multiplicative dynamics of complex systems,

363
0:16:55.121,000 --> 0:16:58,000
tends towards, inexorably, inequality,

364
0:16:58.649,000 --> 0:17:02,000
concentration and collapse.

365
0:17:03.07,000 --> 0:17:05,000
The work of democracies

366
0:17:05.518,000 --> 0:17:09,000
is to maximize the inclusion of the many

367
0:17:10.021,000 --> 0:17:12,000
in order to create prosperity,

368
0:17:12.998,000 --> 0:17:15,000
not to enable the few to accumulate money.

369
0:17:16.92,000 --> 0:17:19,000
Government does create prosperity and growth,

370
0:17:20.02,000 --> 0:17:23,000
by creating the conditions that allow

371
0:17:23.246,000 --> 0:17:25,000
both entrepreneurs and their customers

372
0:17:26.137,000 --> 0:17:27,000
to thrive.

373
0:17:27.982,000 --> 0:17:3,000
Balancing the power of capitalists like me

374
0:17:31.166,000 --> 0:17:34,000
and workers isn't bad for capitalism.

375
0:17:34.338,000 --> 0:17:35,000
It's essential to it.

376
0:17:36.138,000 --> 0:17:38,000
Programs like a reasonable minimum wage,

377
0:17:38.804,000 --> 0:17:4,000
affordable healthcare,

378
0:17:40.818,000 --> 0:17:41,000
paid sick leave,

379
0:17:42.121,000 --> 0:17:45,000
and the progressive taxation necessary

380
0:17:45.54,000 --> 0:17:47,000
to pay for the important infrastructure

381
0:17:47.736,000 --> 0:17:51,000
necessary for the middle class like education, R and D,

382
0:17:51.787,000 --> 0:17:53,000
these are indispensable tools

383
0:17:54.353,000 --> 0:17:56,000
shrewd capitalists should embrace

384
0:17:56.462,000 --> 0:17:59,000
to drive growth, because no one benefits from it

385
0:18:00.448,000 --> 0:18:01,000
like us.

386
0:18:02.094,000 --> 0:18:04,000
Many economists would have you believe

387
0:18:04.342,000 --> 0:18:07,000
that their field is an objective science.

388
0:18:07.422,000 --> 0:18:09,000
I disagree, and I think that it is equally

389
0:18:10.269,000 --> 0:18:12,000
a tool that humans use

390
0:18:12.338,000 --> 0:18:13,000
to enforce and encode

391
0:18:14.227,000 --> 0:18:17,000
our social and moral preferences and prejudices

392
0:18:17.803,000 --> 0:18:2,000
about status and power,

393
0:18:21.705,000 --> 0:18:23,000
which is why plutocrats like me

394
0:18:23.982,000 --> 0:18:27,000
have always needed to find persuasive stories

395
0:18:27.988,000 --> 0:18:28,000
to tell everyone else

396
0:18:29.662,000 --> 0:18:33,000
about why our relative positions

397
0:18:33.776,000 --> 0:18:37,000
are morally righteous and good for everyone:

398
0:18:37.908,000 --> 0:18:41,000
like, we are indispensable, the job creators,

399
0:18:42.183,000 --> 0:18:44,000
and you are not;

400
0:18:44.545,000 --> 0:18:47,000
like, tax cuts for us create growth,

401
0:18:47.931,000 --> 0:18:49,000
but investments in you

402
0:18:49.945,000 --> 0:18:5,000
will balloon our debt

403
0:18:51.621,000 --> 0:18:53,000
and bankrupt our great country;

404
0:18:54.129,000 --> 0:18:55,000
that we matter;

405
0:18:55.997,000 --> 0:18:57,000
that you don't.

406
0:18:58.348,000 --> 0:19:,000
For thousands of years, these stories were called

407
0:19:00.991,000 --> 0:19:01,000
divine right.

408
0:19:02.439,000 --> 0:19:06,000
Today, we have trickle-down economics.

409
0:19:06.693,000 --> 0:19:09,000
How obviously, transparently self-serving

410
0:19:10.576,000 --> 0:19:11,000
all of this is.

411
0:19:12.17,000 --> 0:19:14,000
We plutocrats need to see

412
0:19:14.952,000 --> 0:19:16,000
that the United States of America made us,

413
0:19:17.305,000 --> 0:19:18,000
not the other way around;

414
0:19:18.989,000 --> 0:19:2,000
that a thriving middle class is the source

415
0:19:21.827,000 --> 0:19:23,000
of prosperity in capitalist economies,

416
0:19:24.123,000 --> 0:19:26,000
not a consequence of it.

417
0:19:26.762,000 --> 0:19:28,000
And we should never forget

418
0:19:29.453,000 --> 0:19:32,000
that even the best of us in the worst of circumstances

419
0:19:33.148,000 --> 0:19:38,000
are barefoot by the side of a dirt road selling fruit.

420
0:19:38.882,000 --> 0:19:4,000
Fellow plutocrats, I think it may be time for us

421
0:19:41.496,000 --> 0:19:43,000
to recommit to our country,

422
0:19:43.699,000 --> 0:19:45,000
to commit to a new kind of capitalism

423
0:19:46.261,000 --> 0:19:5,000
which is both more inclusive and more effective,

424
0:19:50.615,000 --> 0:19:52,000
a capitalism that will ensure

425
0:19:52.673,000 --> 0:19:55,000
that America's economy remains

426
0:19:55.834,000 --> 0:19:58,000
the most dynamic and prosperous in the world.

427
0:19:59.22,000 --> 0:20:01,000
Let's secure the future for ourselves,

428
0:20:01.38,000 --> 0:20:03,000
our children and their children.

429
0:20:04.114,000 --> 0:20:07,000
Or alternatively, we could do nothing,

430
0:20:07.162,000 --> 0:20:09,000
hide in our gated communities

431
0:20:09.243,000 --> 0:20:11,000
and private schools,

432
0:20:12.1,000 --> 0:20:14,000
enjoy our planes and yachts

433
0:20:14.136,000 --> 0:20:16,000
— they're fun —

434
0:20:16.476,000 --> 0:20:17,000
and wait for the pitchforks.

435
0:20:18.287,000 --> 0:20:19,000
Thank you.

436
0:20:19.81,000 --> 0:20:2,000
(Applause)

